title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1989-07-15
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Greatest Story Ever Told, Candyman, Walkin' Blues, Peggy-O, Queen Jane Approximately, We Can Run But We Can't Hide, Bird Song

Set 2

Foolish Heart, Victim Or The Crime, Crazy Fingers > Truckin' > Smokestack Lightning > Drums > Jam > China Doll > All Along The Watchtower > Stella Blue > Sugar Magnolia

E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Mecca Deer Creek was the meet up b4 Alpine Valley and I mean everybody ended up in Alpine. It was a HUGE sprawling village in the middle of nowhere but it had everything we needed. The sound system was good and loud at Deer Creek n only got better in Alpine Valley. This sound board is great. I love it when you can hear Phil with that warm bottom hum. Tiger sounds great here. Now Jerry might flub a vocal, but Tiger is not missing a beat. The board really put's you right there and the band is working top of their game.
